From: VyOS LS1046A maintainers <ls1046a@vyos.local>
Date: 2026-05-27
Subject: [PATCH] DPAA1 AF_XDP pool: remove LIODN sanity gate (arm64 has no fsl,liodn)

Patch 0075a added a LIODN sanity arm to af_xdp_pool_xsk_pool_attach()
that rejected an XSK pool attach if fman_port_get_liodn(rxp) returned 0,
on the assumption that this would indicate a malformed DT or an
unprobed fman_port.

That assumption was wrong on arm64 LS1046A.  On this platform:

  * The PAMU IOMMU is programmed by U-Boot at boot into firmware bypass
    mode.  The Linux fsl_pamu driver (drivers/iommu/fsl_pamu.c) is gated
    by Kconfig "PPC_E500MC || (COMPILE_TEST && PPC)" and does not build
    on arm64.  No per-LIODN window programming happens from Linux.

  * The Mono Gateway DT (mono-gateway-dk.dts + fsl-ls1046a.dtsi) carries
    NO fsl,liodn properties on any FMan port.  Verified on a v4.3 ISO
    DUT by walking /proc/device-tree/soc/fman@1a00000/port@*/ -- only
    cell-index, compatible, name, phandle, reg are present.  Zero
    fsl,liodn nodes.

  * Therefore port->dts_params.fman->liodn_base[port_id] is 0 and
    fman_port_get_liodn() returns 0.  The 0075a `!liodn` branch fires
    on EVERY XSK pool attach, returning -ENODEV.

This was caught at M2 validation on 2026-05-27, ISO 2026.05.26-2338,
kernel 6.18.33-vyos: bind(XDP_ZEROCOPY) on eth4 q0 returned -ENODEV(19)
because dpaa_setup_xsk_pool -> ops->xsk_pool_attach -> 0075a `!liodn`
arm short-circuited the path before xsk_pool_dma_map() in 0075b could
run.

The 0075a patch header itself anticipated this:

  "Note on PAMU (spec sec 4.6): the spec assumed a per-attach
   fsl_pamu_window_create()/_destroy() API.  Mainline 6.18.31's
   drivers/iommu/fsl_pamu.c is gated by Kconfig dependency
   'PPC_E500MC || (COMPILE_TEST && PPC)' and does not build on arm64.
   On arm64 LS1046A the PAMU runs in firmware-programmed bypass and
   the FMan masters DMA directly to physical RAM via dma-direct -
   xsk_pool_dma_map() in 0075b will be sufficient.  No per-window
   PAMU programming is required."

...but the same patch kept the LIODN check as a "DTS sanity gate".
That gate is incompatible with the documented arm64 DT shape.

This patch removes the LIODN read + check entirely.  Rationale:

  1. The value was never going to be consumed -- no caller of
     fman_port_get_liodn() in the AF_XDP path uses the returned value
     for anything (PAMU window programming was the only consumer and
     it does not exist on arm64).

  2. A non-zero liodn would not have indicated anything useful either:
     the DT could carry an arbitrary fsl,liodn value and bypass-mode
     PAMU would ignore it.  So as a sanity check the arm is also
     value-free.

  3. The fman_port * + priv->mac_dev * sanity checks immediately above
     still cover the "fman_port unprobed" and "mac_dev unbound" failure
     modes (those return -ENODEV with xsk_pamu_window_fail bumped, as
     before).  Removing the LIODN arm does not weaken the defence
     against those genuine misconfigurations.

  4. The fman_port_get_liodn() accessor and its EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL stay
     in fman_port.c (added by 0075a).  Removing it from arm64 callers
     does not regress any other in-tree user; there are none today.
     A future PowerPC port of this code (or an arm64 fsl_pamu driver
     reintroduction) can reintroduce the check then -- ideally as a
     warn-once + degraded mode rather than fail-closed.

Behaviour after this patch:

  * bind(XDP_ZEROCOPY) on eth4 q0 progresses past the LIODN arm.
  * The next gate is queue_id < priv->xsk_max_qbands, which is set to
    4 at probe by patch 0077.  q0..q3 are accepted; q4+ rejected with
    -EINVAL and xsk_pool_attach_fail bumped (correct behaviour).
  * 0075b's xsk_pool_dma_map(), bman_new_pool(), 8192-chunk seed loop,
    and rcu_assign_pointer(priv->xsk_pool[queue_id], pool) all run as
    designed.  priv->xsk_pool_attach_ok increments on success.

Spec impact: section 5.3 step 1 ("validate constraints") drops the
LIODN bullet.  The xsk_pamu_window_fail counter is now only bumped by
the `!priv->mac_dev` and `!rxp` arms above -- both genuine error
conditions that should be debugged at the DT level if they ever fire.

Acceptance gate (M2):
  - bind(XDP_ZEROCOPY) on eth4 q0 returns 0 with eth4 MTU <= 3290
    and chunk_size=4096 headroom=0 (frame_size 3840 == DPAA1_MIN_UMEM_CHUNK).
  - 100x attach/detach stress on the same UMEM does not crash the
    core driver or leak BMan pools (verified via bman_get_count() on
    a private BPID, after the dedicated XSK BMan channel work in 0080).

Build-verified clean against linux-6.18.31 with the full 0068..0077
patch series applied first.

Signed-off-by: VyOS LS1046A maintainers <ls1046a@vyos.local>
---
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/af_xdp_pool/af_xdp_pool_main.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/af_xdp_pool/af_xdp_pool_main.c
index 0e3f7b980..16afb1dcd 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/af_xdp_pool/af_xdp_pool_main.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/af_xdp_pool/af_xdp_pool_main.c
@@ -117,7 +117,6 @@ u32 frame_size, headroom;
 struct bman_pool *bpool;
 int ret;
 u32 seeded, batch, n, i;
-u32 liodn;
 
 if (!priv || !pool)
 return -EINVAL;
@@ -152,11 +151,13 @@ return -EINVAL;
 }
 
 /*
- * LIODN sanity check: prove the RX FMan port is bound to its parent
- * FMan and that DT carries a non-zero fsl,liodn for this port.  The
- * value isn't consumed yet (no arm64 PAMU driver in mainline), but
- * a zero return here means either DT is malformed or fman_port has
- * not yet probed - both fail-closed conditions.
+ * fman_port + mac_dev sanity checks: prove the RX FMan port is bound to
+ * its parent FMan.  The LIODN sanity arm that used to follow was removed
+ * by patch 0075c: on arm64 LS1046A the Mono Gateway DT carries no
+ * fsl,liodn properties on FMan ports, the fsl_pamu driver is PPC-only,
+ * and the value was never consumed in our DMA path (xsk_pool_dma_map()
+ * via dma-direct in step 2 below is sufficient on the CoreNet-coherent
+ * fabric).
  */
 if (!priv->mac_dev) {
 priv->xsk_pamu_window_fail++;
@@ -169,13 +170,6 @@ if (!rxp) {
 priv->xsk_pamu_window_fail++;
 priv->xsk_pool_attach_fail++;
 return -ENODEV;
-}
-
-liodn = fman_port_get_liodn(rxp);
-if (!liodn) {
-priv->xsk_pamu_window_fail++;
-priv->xsk_pool_attach_fail++;
-return -ENODEV;
 }
 
